"reasoning-term-text\">劉鎮軍</span> - Liu Zhenjun, a title.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-12\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">武帝</span> - Emperor Wu of Liu Song.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-20\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">吳興俞亮</span> - Yu Liang of Wuxing.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-21\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">秣陵令中山劉沼</span> - Liu Zhao of Zhongshan, magistrate of Moling.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-22\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">零陵太守廣陵劉興道</span> - Liu Xingdao of Guangling, governor of Lingling.</li></ul>\n</section>"},{"marker":"4","safeMarker":"4","html":"<p><span class=\"marker-text\">[4]</span></p><section class=\"reasoning-section\">\n  <p class=\"reasoning-section-title\"><strong>Idiomatic Expressions</strong></p>\n  <ul class=\"reasoning-section-list\"><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-1\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">晋陵无锡尉</span> - Refers to a local official in the Jinling region (modern-day Zhenjiang, Jiangsu).</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-2\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">贮谷，后开乃成蛇草</span> - Metaphorical or supernatural event where stored grain transforms into snake grass.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-3\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">焚之，使贫</span> - Burning the snake grass causes poverty as a consequence.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-4\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">官须发为矛旄</span> - The official needs hair for a spear flag, a ceremonial item.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-5\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">今居黄氏居，非意伤我目</span> - Now it resides in Huang&#39;s home, unintentionally hurting my eyes, likely a curse or supernatural event.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-6\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">尝出行，憩于台城东橘树下</span> - He once traveled and rested under an orange tree east of Taicheng.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-7\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">薄晚，遣婢与法公相闻</span> - Late in the afternoon, she sent a maid to inform Fagong.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-8\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">方夕欲诣宿</span> - She wanted to stay overnight as evening approached.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-9\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">人定后，乃来</span> - After the hour of people had settled, she came.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-10\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">自称姓檀，住在城侧</span> - She introduced herself as surnamed Tan, living on the outskirts of the city.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-11\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">因共眠寝，至晓而去</span> - They slept together until dawn and then she left.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-12\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">明日复来</span> - The next day, she came again.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-13\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">如此数夜</span> - This happened for several nights.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-14\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">每晓去，婢辄来迎</span> - Every morning when she left, the maid would come to greet her.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-15\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">复有男子可六七岁，端丽可爱</span> - There was also a boy, about six or seven years old, who was very handsome and lovely.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-16\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">女云是其弟</span> - The woman said he was her brother.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-17\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">后晓去，女衣裙开，见龟尾及龟脚</span> - The next morning when she left, the woman&#39;s skirt opened, revealing a turtle&#39;s tail and feet, likely a supernatural revelation.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-18\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">法公方悟是魅</span> - Fagong then realized she was a spirit.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-19\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">欲执之</span> - He wanted to seize her.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-20\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">向夕复来</span> - As evening approached, she came again.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-21\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">即然火照觅，寻失所在</span> - He immediately lit a fire to search for her, but she was gone.</li></ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"reasoning-section\">\n  <p class=\"reasoning-section-title\"><strong>Cultural and Historical Allusions</strong></p>\n  <ul class=\"reasoning-section-list\"><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-22\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">竟陵王诞</span> - Refers to King Jingling Duan, likely Liu Duan, a prince during the Southern Song dynasty.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-23\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">广记引作刘诞</span> - The *Guangji* (Comprehensive Records) refers to him as Liu Duan.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-24\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">山阴朱法公者</span> - Zhu Fagong of Shanyin, a historical figure.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-25\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">台城东橘树下</span> - Refers to an orange tree east of Taicheng, a historical location.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-26\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">黄氏</span> - Refers to a woman surnamed Huang, likely a historical figure.</li></ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"reasoning-section\">\n  <p class=\"reasoning-section-title\"><strong>Proper Nouns</strong></p>\n  <ul class=\"reasoning-section-list\"><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-27\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">严无欲</span> - A proper name, likely a historical figure, but his exact identity is unclear.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-28\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">蛇草</span> - Could refer to a type of plant associated with snakes or a curse.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-29\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">刘诞</span> - A proper name, likely referring to Liu Duan, a prince during the Southern Song dynasty.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-30\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">朱法公</span> - A proper name, likely referring to Zhu Fagong, a historical figure.</li><li class=\"reasoning-term-item\" data-term-key=\"term-31\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\" aria-pressed=\"false\"><span class=\"reasoning-term-text\">檀</span> - A proper surname, likely referring to a historical figure.</li></ul>\n</section>"}]
